// The original bug-report scenario: `.exit` (missing trailing ':') after
// `} always` becomes `Op::Instruction { mnemonic: ".exit", operand: None }`,
// which `prune_unreachable_instructions` then drops as dead code — before
// `emit_object`'s `EncodeError::UnknownMnemonic` enrichment can see it.
// The peephole pass detects the dot-prefix-no-operand shape and emits the
// label-declaration-style warning so the user gets the same advice they
// would get for the typo in normal straight-line code. A trailing `nop`
// produces the generic flavour, demonstrating both diagnostics coexist.

func test @a8 @i8 {
    {
        lda #1
    } always
.exit
    nop
}
